					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">The Latest on Dot/Kiting</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=17286" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    Geoffrey Zatkin, Verant Game Designer discusses the latest on Damage Over Time spells and Kiting.
<blockquote>
<p>
If you are getting this mail, it is because you e-mailed me concerning the recent modifications to DoT spells in reference to Kiting on the test server. I am sorry that you are getting a group reply, but there were too many e-mails to respond to each of you individually. 
I did want, however, for you all to at least get a response. </p>
<p>
DoT spells will most likely be changed with the next patch. I can not go in to detail about what they changes are yet - we are still testing and do not want to prematurely announce what we will do. </p>
<p>
Be assured that the changes will not eliminate Kiting, nor will they make DoT spells useless. For many people, the changes that we make will increase the power of your DoT spells. For those of you that kite, you will lose a bit of efficiency kiting. </p>
<p>
Kiting in its current state is bad for the game because it allows certain classes to take out creatures of levels that other classes have absolutely no chance of taking out. This kind of imbalance is not something that we want in EQ. </p>
<p>
The reason that we are putting these changes in now is that we finally heard a solution that we found acceptable AND that had minimal impact on the rest of the game. Most other suggestions involved getting rid of or limiting SoW (which would effect everybody) or getting rid of all movement spells together. Kiting in its most common form involves SoW and a DoT. Kiting can also be done with Snare and DD or a Bow, the Necromancer Darkness series, Journeyman boots and DD, Root Bombing, etc. Any time that you can move faster then your opponent, there is trouble (and you are doing some form of kiting). If we were going to completely fix kiting, we would have to take EVERY instance that let you move faster then a monster and fix it. That would have a huge impact on EQ - we do not want to do it. </p>
<p>
We have a change that has a much softer impact going in - look for our announcement about it soon. I think you will be pleasantly surprised about what we are doing - at least compared to what you probably think we are due to rampant rumors. </p>
<p>
As a side note, we played with different powers of DoT's and Kiting on the test server. People saw this and started posting. Now, just as a reminder, test is for testing. Thank you all for your prompt e-mails noticing that were we testing DoT spells. Please realize in the future that just because we are testing something on test does not mean that it will go live. </p>
<p>
As a side note, we think that we got most of the DoT bug fixed. This means that you will be able to use your DoT's in a party situation, making your class much more powerful (the Necro's should be very happy with this one). I have heard reports that there still may be a case where there is a bug - but it happens MUCH less frequently. If you experience this bug, please e-mail use a report of what spells you were using, what you were fighting, the classes in your party and the size of your party. Any info (the more specific the better) you can give us on this bug (if it exists) would be greatly appreciated. Please e-mail this to <a href="mailto:ggrobson@verant.com">ggrobson@verant.com</a>. This address is ONLY for bugs related to DoT spells.</p> 
<p>
If you still have issues with this, please wait a week or two before e-mailing me. I have a backlog of e-mail that I want to get answered - e-mailing me later will ensure that I have more time to read what you send me. </p>
<p>
Have a good one, and feel free to repost this. <p>
<p>
Geoffrey C. Zatkin<br>
Arch-Mage of Norrath 
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
